betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Whilst surviving here I caught a glimpse of a light source on a dark structure off in the distance at night. I should probably check this out as there might be decent resources in the building.

This quest will complete when you arrive at the Biotite Refuge.

Now it's simple: Create a Cobblestone Generator using any shape or method you want, and bask in the glory of an infinite supply of Cobblestone.

Submit some infinite Cobblestone.

If you haven't yet, complete all the other available quests. Some of them provide large amounts of Cobblestone that will save you the grinding for this quest.

I have recieved a signal from a location southeast from here. Perhaps I should go check it out?

This quest will complete when you arrive at the Gaia Shrine.

Back when this world was whole, explorers built a shrine in the deepest part of the densest jungle. I bet there is some treasure there for me.

This quest will complete when you arrive at the Ancient's Shrine.

I've been detecting some strange cold winds coming from the area southwest of the island. Could be worth checking out.

This quest will complete when you visit the Glacial Monument.

Legends speak of an ancient tomb housing treasures and fortunes.

This quest will complete when you visit the Deity's Temple.

Sieving different blocks result in different results. Even using different meshes will result in different items too!

You can use JEI's Recipe Lookup mode to determine what mesh combined with what block will produce what items, and the percentages to do so.
Creating an Iron Stiffened Mesh will allow you to get even finer materials from Dust.

Suntanning for sundries.

Create some Drying Racks. You can hang various meats on Drying Racksto turn them into Jerky. Create some Monster Jerky in this way.

Good morning! Time to start your adventure!

A good place to start would be to knock down this tree you're on.

Once you do, make some Planks.

Yeah man.

Craft a Wooden Hammer.

Very concentrated evil!

Craft a Compressed Crook. It's nine times more expensive than a Crook, but it feels about nine times more effective, too.

What're you lookin' at?

Craft a Crook.

Clay is the cornerstone to all new innovation in this world.

Place a Dust block in a barrel completely filled with Water. It'll turn to clay.

To make a Bucket, you simply need to craft it using Clay. However, to make the Unfired Crucible, you'll need to use Porcelain Clay, a solution made from Bone Meal and Clay.
To get Porcelain Clay, you'll need Bone Meal.

Get it?

Craft a Wooden Barrel. Once you do, you can fill it with compostable materialsto create Dirt. Examples of compostable materials include String, Saplings, and Wheat.

If a machine can do something, you shouldn't have to.

Craft a Cobblestone Generator. Place a Chest on it as its output location.

Finally, it's time to get some metals.

Sieving Gravel through a Flint Stiffened Mesh has chances to drop various Ore Pieces. Gather these quantities of these Ore Pieces.

Then, craft together 4 Ore Pieces to get an Ore Chunk. An Ore Chunk is functionally similar to an Ore you would find underground, but in an item form.

Your current mesh is simply not powerful enough to get more valuable resources out of blocks. Time to change that.

You can craft 3 Gravel together to collect a Flint. Use it to craft a Flint Stiffened Mesh.

Things are starting to heat up in here.

Cook your Buckets and Crucible in a Furnace and they'll be usable.

You'll find further progression impossible without a Furnace; The Sun can't cook all materials to the required temperatures.

Create a Furnace. Make some Charcoal using it.

And with that, you'll have metal.

Smelt Ore Chunks to get Ingots.

Only one more step away from unlimited Cobblestone.

Remember! The Clay Bucket will break after a single use with hot liquid! So I would recommend moving the Water first.

The Heavy Sieve allows you to sift Compressed blocks, like Compressed Dirt.

Craft one.

Get used to this fun activity!

Craft a Sieve and a Mesh. You can run various "powdery" blocks through this to get fine materials, like Pebbles out of Dirt. Speaking of Pebbles, collect 4 of them. Craft them together to get a Cobblestone block!
With this, the finest-grain sieve and the finest-grain block, you can get Yellorium.
You can now make the ultimate mesh. The Diamond Stiffened Mesh. This will vastly increase the drop rates of any siftable items.

Oh my.

Much like a Compressed Crook, you can create a Compressed Hammer. It's nine times as expensive as a Hammer, but it's nine times as powerful.

See all those good-for-nothing Leaves? Time we make something out of them.

Breaking Leaves with your Crook or Compressed Crook will allow you to gather special items. You'll also get more Saplings this way. Repeat this until you can get a Silkworm.

Right clicking Leaves with a Silkworm will infest them. Wait until the entire tree is as infested as it can get, and then break the Infested Leaves with your Crook or Compressed Crook. It'll drop String.

We can fill a Barrel with Rainwater! But if it's not raining, there's another process you can do.

Place Sand on a Drying Rack. Wait 45 seconds, and it'll transform into Glass.

You can create glass bottles out of this, and transfer the Water out of your tree's pond into Barrels using the Bottles.

YEAH, MAN!

Breaking down Cobblestone with a Hammer will result in finer-grain blocks. Depending on how many times you repeat the process will dictate which block you get as a return.

Break Cobblestone down to Gravel, Gravel down to Sand, and Sand down to Dust.

Casting is the process of filling a mold with a metal and letting it harden into that shape. This will be our way of extracting material from the Smeltery.

Craft an Ingot Cast by placing an "Ingot-shaped" item in the Casting Table, and pouring either Molten Gold or Molten Aluminum Brass on it by right-clicking the faucet. Then, when the cast is made, you can pour molten metals into the Ingot Cast to get an ingot back.

Remember, it's not limited to just Ingots! You can use many shapes, like Pickaxe Heads, Gems, and Signs. You can use these to assist in Tinkers' Construct tool creation.

The next step will be to build a processor capable of handling large amounts of ore. A Smeltery will do this job nicely.

First, craft up a lot of Grout.

Next, smelt it into Seared Bricks.

Finally, craft the required components of a Smeltery. If you don't know how to build one, you can refer to your Materials and You book.

Delicious!

Smashing any compressed block with a Compressed Hammer will perform the "crushing" process on that block, dropping nine of the next tier below's appropriate resource block.

These vanilla tools seem pretty weak... And you can barely customize them! Time to change that!

First, create these Patterns using Tinker's Construct's tables.

Then, use them to create some parts.

If you have any concerns about how to use or create the required tables, refer to your Materials and You book.

Metal mixing is exciting!

1 Gold + 1 SSilver = 2 Electrum
2 Iron + 1 Nickel = 3 Invar
3 Copper + 1 Tin = 4 Bronze

You can find more alloys using JEI's Recipe Lookup mode.

Blend automation and coin minting automation. This one has it all. Alloying, mob farms, mining. It's the jack-of-all-trades.

Remember that the coins you create for this quest aren't useless. You can put them in a Numismatic Dynamo to create power!

Create an Enderium Coin, and two blends to indicate sufficient completion of this mod.

Remember! This mod is a lot deeper than this, but there's a lot of progress you can make that can't be quantified.
Create a Chaotic Core to indicate you have completed Draconic Evolution.
Craft the sacred Kikoku to indicate completion of Extra Utilities 2.

Kind of ironic. One of the hardest things to automate is one of the first materials to generate.

Plus Rainbow Generators! Those are probably fun to automate.
Kill the Gaia Spirit and create a Gaia Spirit Ingot to show you've completed Botania's content sufficiently.

This mod makes it hard, but automation is extra fun with this! Try it.

Remember, the Gaia Spirit feels impossible to automate, and it is. So don't waste your time for only 16 ingots.
Hope you can figure out how to automate Fusion Crafting. Try it!

You can use the locations identified in the quests in this chapter to point you to structures
lost in the void, like ruins or monuments.

There are rewards at the locations waiting for you!

This chapter will serve as your starting ground for how you can play a modded Skyblock pack.

After this chapter, things get a little bit more freeform.
You've finished the basic tutorials. The world is your oyster.
